contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|FX|Fx|fx}} '''FX''', '''F/X''', '''Fx''', or '''fx''' may refer to: {{tocright}} == Entertainment == * [[FX (TV channel)]], an international cable/satellite television network (see article for channels by country) * ''[[F/X]]'', a movie set in the world of special effects * ''[[F/X: The Series]]'', a television program based on the movie * [[FX (comics)]], a comic book series published by IDW, drawn by artist John Byrne * "FX", a song by Black Sabbath on the album ''[[Black Sabbath Vol. 4]]'' * [[f(x) (band)]], South Korean girl group == Technology == * [[Athlon 64 FX]], a variant of the AMD Athlon 64 microprocessor * [[Infiniti FX]], model designation for Infiniti's compact luxury Crossover Utility Vehicles * [[Toyota Kijang]] or Tamaraw FX, a sport utility vehicle * FX format, Nikon's nomenclature for the [[full-frame digital SLR]] * [[Software framework |Framework]] for software development, most notably the [[.NET Framework |Microsoft .NET]] (“dotNetFx”); in particular, “WinFX” was pre-release codename of .NET 3.0 * [[Mozilla Firefox]] (abbreviated to Fx or fx), a web browser * "Effects", as in [[special effect]]s, sound effects and guitar effects * [[Super FX]], a graphics chip used in certain Super Nintendo games, notably Star Fox, to accelerate the rendering of polygonal models == Other == * [[Bone fracture]], in medical shorthand * [[Factor X]], a protein involved in coagulation * [[FedEx Express]], IATA airline designator * [[Foreign exchange market]], a banking term for changing money from one currency into another * The [[Forward price|forward exchange rate]], in economics shorthand * [[Foreign exchange service (telecommunications)]], a telephone connection to a distant exchange * [[Francis Xavier]] (1506–1552), Basque saint and co-founder of the Jesuits * [[Fuji Xerox]], Japanese document company * [[FX (trade magazine)]], a UK trade magazine * [[FX (Fighter Experimental)]], two specifications for two US Naval fighter projects * An abbreviation for the French given name [[François-Xavier]] * The unofficial designation of the [[Holden 48-215]], the first automobile by Australian company [[Holden]] * [[fX Sudirman]], mall in South Jakarta ==See also== * [[SFX (disambiguation)]] * [[EFX (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
